Package: coevolve
Title: Fit Bayesian Generalized Dynamic Phylogenetic Models using 'Stan' or 'JAX'
Version: 1.0.0.9001
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Scott", "Claessens", , "scott.claessens@gmail.com", 
             role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3562-6981")),
      person("Erik", "Ringen", , "erikjacob.ringen@uzh.ch", 
             role = c("aut")))
Description: Fit Bayesian generalized dynamic phylogenetic models
    using 'Stan' or 'JAX'. The package allows an arbitrary number
    of variables with different response distributions to coevolve
    on a phylogenetic tree via an Ornstein-Uhlenbeck evolutionary
    process, allowing users to assess directionality between
    coevolving variables. The optional JAX backend enables
    high-performance sampling with NumPyro and potential GPU
    acceleration via 'reticulate'.
